Seven tugs will attempt to refloat theSouth Korean motor bulk carrier Hyundai New World tonight,Lloyds shipping intelligence service said in its latest update.    The vessel grounded close to Itaqui port in Brazil lastnight after undocking from Ponta da Madeira terminal.    Lloyds said the 200,000 dwt vessel is carrying about180,000 tons of ore.    Five holds are partially flooded and there is some leakageof bunkers from double bottom tanks. At low water tide thevessel has a list of five degrees to port and the listincreases as the tide rises.    Reuter&#3;